There are nine fielding positions in <a href="baseball">baseball</a>. Each <a href="Baseball%20scorekeeping%23Defensive%20positions">position</a> conventionally has an associated number, which is used <a href="official%20scorer">to score</a> <a href="putout">putout</a>s: 3 

1 (<a href="pitcher">pitcher</a>), 2 (<a href="catcher">catcher</a>), 3 (<a href="first%20baseman">first baseman</a>), 4 (<a href="second%20baseman">second baseman</a>), 5 (<a href="third%20baseman">third baseman</a>), 6 (<a href="shortstop">shortstop</a>), 7 (<a href="left%20fielder">left fielder</a>), 8 (<a href="center%20fielder">center fielder</a>), and 9 (<a href="right%20fielder">right fielder</a>).

