Usually the <a href="mode%20%28statistics%29">mode</a> of a binomial "B"("n", "p") distribution is equal to formula_38, where formula_39 is the <a href="floor%20function">floor function</a>. However, when ("n" + 1)"p" is an integer and "p" is neither 0 nor 1, then the distribution has two modes: ("n" + 1)"p" and ("n" + 1)"p" − 1. When "p" is equal to 0 or 1, the mode will be 0 and "n" correspondingly. These cases can be summarized as follows:

