This is proved using the method of types (see for example chapter 12 of Elements of Information Theory by Cover and Thomas ).

We can also change the formula_100 in the denominator to formula_101, by approximating the binomial coefficient with Stirlings formula.

This distribution was derived by <a href="James%20Bernoulli">James Bernoulli</a> in 1713. He considered the case where p = r/(r+s) where p is the probability of sucess and r and s are positive integers. <a href="Blaise%20Pascal">Blaise Pascal</a> had earlier considered the case where p = 1/2.




